validateGuess

public static int validateGuess(Cube[] c,
                                String word,
                                Dictionary d)
Determine if the specified word guess by user is a valid guess and a valid word. A valid guess (1) must be in the dictionary, (2) must not have been used before, and (3) must contain the letters of the word on the cube faces in a left to right order. These checks are performed in the order given.

Parameters:
word - guess made by the user
Returns:
score of a valid word (sum of the point values of the letters)
0 if the word is not in the dictionary
-1 if the word has been previously guessed
-2 if the word is not found in the cubes
